{"questionId":"13420139","questionHtml":"<p>Write&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>&nbsp;in the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>r</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></msup></math>,&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>524</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for the correct modulus and <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for the correct argument.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13420139","referenceCode":"23N.1.AHL.TZ0.8a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write z in the form z=reθi, where r∈ℝ+, -π<θ≤π.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers introduction","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaV